    "updated_at": "2014-09-03T19:00:12Z",
    "body": "I think it's probably a good idea to remove `retry()` around calls that can't return `EINTR`. At the very least, it avoids confusion when the reader sees `retry()` and believes that means the call can in fact return `EINTR`. @alexcrichton?\n",
