    "created_at": "2014-09-04T03:01:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-04T03:01:16Z",
    "body": "I'm a little wary with this in that are we 100% certain that every single implementation of these syscalls will _never_ return `EINTR`? I certainly agree that according to the documentation in the linked manpages none of these can return `EINTR`, however!\n\nRegardless, it's pretty easy to add these all back at a later date, so I'm ok removing them for now because in theory any compliant implementation won't return `EINTR`.\n",
